net.dean.jraw.models

Class FauxListing<T extends RedditObject>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dean.jraw.models.JsonModel
      • net.dean.jraw.models.RedditObject
        • net.dean.jraw.models.Listing<T>
          • net.dean.jraw.models.FauxListing<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of elements that will be in this listing
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.List<T>

    public final class FauxListing<T extends RedditObject>
extends Listing<T>
    This class is used to imitate a Listing without parsing any JSON. This class essentially exposes Listing's protected constructor, enabling data to be fed directly to internal fields.
